The paper focuses on the impact of membership turnover and social capital losses on productivity in online communities, which is a topic that falls under the scope of social computing (cs.SOC) and computational social science (cs.CY). The study also involves the analysis of social networks, which is a common theme in the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and systems and control (cs.SD). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of member withdrawal on project outcomes, which is a topic that could be relevant to the sub-category of computer and society (cs.CC).
